1755static Instruction *canonicalizeConstantArg0ToArg1(CallInst &Call) {
1756 assert(Call.getNumArgOperands() > 1 && "Need at least 2 args to swap");
1757 Value *Arg0 = Call.getArgOperand(0), *Arg1 = Call.getArgOperand(1);
1758 if (isa<Constant>(Arg0) && !isa<Constant>(Arg1)) {
1759 Call.setArgOperand(0, Arg1);
1760 Call.setArgOperand(1, Arg0);
1761 return &Call;
1762 }
1763 return nullptr;
1764}
1765
1766Instruction *InstCombiner::foldIntrinsicWithOverflowCommon(IntrinsicInst *II) {
1767 WithOverflowInst *WO = cast<WithOverflowInst>(II);
1768 Value *OperationResult = nullptr;
1769 Constant *OverflowResult = nullptr;
1770 if (OptimizeOverflowCheck(WO->getBinaryOp(), WO->isSigned(), WO->getLHS(),
1771 WO->getRHS(), *WO, OperationResult, OverflowResult))
1772 return CreateOverflowTuple(WO, OperationResult, OverflowResult);
1773 return nullptr;
1774}
1775
1776/// CallInst simplification. This mostly only handles folding of intrinsic
1777/// instructions. For normal calls, it allows visitCallBase to do the heavy
1778/// lifting.
1779Instruction *InstCombiner::visitCallInst(CallInst &CI) {
1780 if (Value *V = SimplifyCall(&CI, SQ.getWithInstruction(&CI)))
1781 return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, V);
1782
1783 if (isFreeCall(&CI, &TLI))
1784 return visitFree(CI);
1785
1786 // If the caller function is nounwind, mark the call as nounwind, even if the
1787 // callee isn't.
1788 if (CI.getFunction()->doesNotThrow() && !CI.doesNotThrow()) {
1789 CI.setDoesNotThrow();
1790 return &CI;
1791 }
1792
1793 IntrinsicInst *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(&CI);
1794 if (!II) return visitCallBase(CI);
1795
1796 // Intrinsics cannot occur in an invoke or a callbr, so handle them here
1797 // instead of in visitCallBase.
1798 if (auto *MI = dyn_cast<AnyMemIntrinsic>(II)) {
1799 bool Changed = false;
1800
1801 // memmove/cpy/set of zero bytes is a noop.
1802 if (Constant *NumBytes = dyn_cast<Constant>(MI->getLength())) {
1803 if (NumBytes->isNullValue())
1804 return eraseInstFromFunction(CI);
1805
1806 if (ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(NumBytes))
1807 if (CI->getZExtValue() == 1) {
1808 // Replace the instruction with just byte operations. We would
1809 // transform other cases to loads/stores, but we don't know if
1810 // alignment is sufficient.
1811 }
1812 }
1813
1814 // No other transformations apply to volatile transfers.
1815 if (auto *M = dyn_cast<MemIntrinsic>(MI))
1816 if (M->isVolatile())
1817 return nullptr;
1818
1819 // If we have a memmove and the source operation is a constant global,
1820 // then the source and dest pointers can't alias, so we can change this
1821 // into a call to memcpy.
1822 if (auto *MMI = dyn_cast<AnyMemMoveInst>(MI)) {
1823 if (GlobalVariable *GVSrc = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(MMI->getSource()))
1824 if (GVSrc->isConstant()) {
1825 Module *M = CI.getModule();
1826 Intrinsic::ID MemCpyID =
1827 isa<AtomicMemMoveInst>(MMI)
1828 ? Intrinsic::memcpy_element_unordered_atomic
1829 : Intrinsic::memcpy;
1830 Type *Tys[3] = { CI.getArgOperand(0)->getType(),
1831 CI.getArgOperand(1)->getType(),
1832 CI.getArgOperand(2)->getType() };
1833 CI.setCalledFunction(Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, MemCpyID, Tys));
1834 Changed = true;
1835 }
1836 }
1837
1838 if (AnyMemTransferInst *MTI = dyn_cast<AnyMemTransferInst>(MI)) {
1839 // memmove(x,x,size) -> noop.
1840 if (MTI->getSource() == MTI->getDest())
1841 return eraseInstFromFunction(CI);
1842 }
1843
1844 // If we can determine a pointer alignment that is bigger than currently
1845 // set, update the alignment.
1846 if (auto *MTI = dyn_cast<AnyMemTransferInst>(MI)) {
1847 if (Instruction *I = SimplifyAnyMemTransfer(MTI))
1848 return I;
1849 } else if (auto *MSI = dyn_cast<AnyMemSetInst>(MI)) {
1850 if (Instruction *I = SimplifyAnyMemSet(MSI))
1851 return I;
1852 }
1853
1854 if (Changed) return II;
1855 }
1856
1857 // For vector result intrinsics, use the generic demanded vector support.
1858 if (II->getType()->isVectorTy()) {
1859 auto VWidth = II->getType()->getVectorNumElements();
1860 APInt UndefElts(VWidth, 0);
1861 APInt AllOnesEltMask(APInt::getAllOnesValue(VWidth));
1862 if (Value *V = SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(II, AllOnesEltMask, UndefElts)) {
1863 if (V != II)
1864 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, V);
1865 return II;
1866 }
1867 }
1868
1869 if (Instruction *I = SimplifyNVVMIntrinsic(II, *this))
1870 return I;
1871
1872 auto SimplifyDemandedVectorEltsLow = [this](Value *Op, unsigned Width,
1873 unsigned DemandedWidth) {
1874 APInt UndefElts(Width, 0);
1875 APInt DemandedElts = APInt::getLowBitsSet(Width, DemandedWidth);
1876 return SimplifyDemandedVectorElts(Op, DemandedElts, UndefElts);
1877 };
1878
1879 Intrinsic::ID IID = II->getIntrinsicID();
1880 switch (IID) {
1881 default: break;
1882 case Intrinsic::objectsize:
1883 if (Value *V = lowerObjectSizeCall(II, DL, &TLI, /*MustSucceed=*/false))
1884 return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, V);
1885 return nullptr;
1886 case Intrinsic::bswap: {
1887 Value *IIOperand = II->getArgOperand(0);
1888 Value *X = nullptr;
1889
1890 // bswap(trunc(bswap(x))) -> trunc(lshr(x, c))
1891 if (match(IIOperand, m_Trunc(m_BSwap(m_Value(X))))) {
1892 unsigned C = X->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() -
1893 IIOperand->getType()->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
1894 Value *CV = ConstantInt::get(X->getType(), C);
1895 Value *V = Builder.CreateLShr(X, CV);
1896 return new TruncInst(V, IIOperand->getType());
1897 }
1898 break;
1899 }
1900 case Intrinsic::masked_load:
1901 if (Value *SimplifiedMaskedOp = simplifyMaskedLoad(*II))
1902 return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, SimplifiedMaskedOp);
1903 break;
1904 case Intrinsic::masked_store:
1905 return simplifyMaskedStore(*II);
1906 case Intrinsic::masked_gather:
1907 return simplifyMaskedGather(*II);
1908 case Intrinsic::masked_scatter:
1909 return simplifyMaskedScatter(*II);
1910 case Intrinsic::launder_invariant_group:
1911 case Intrinsic::strip_invariant_group:
1912 if (auto *SkippedBarrier = simplifyInvariantGroupIntrinsic(*II, *this))
1913 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, SkippedBarrier);
1914 break;
1915 case Intrinsic::powi:
1916 if (ConstantInt *Power = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(II->getArgOperand(1))) {
1917 // 0 and 1 are handled in instsimplify
1918
1919 // powi(x, -1) -> 1/x
1920 if (Power->isMinusOne())
1921 return BinaryOperator::CreateFDiv(ConstantFP::get(CI.getType(), 1.0),
1922 II->getArgOperand(0));
1923 // powi(x, 2) -> x*x
1924 if (Power->equalsInt(2))
1925 return BinaryOperator::CreateFMul(II->getArgOperand(0),
1926 II->getArgOperand(0));
1927 }
1928 break;
1929
1930 case Intrinsic::cttz:
1931 case Intrinsic::ctlz:
1932 if (auto *I = foldCttzCtlz(*II, *this))
1933 return I;
1934 break;
1935
1936 case Intrinsic::ctpop:
1937 if (auto *I = foldCtpop(*II, *this))
1938 return I;
1939 break;
1940
1941 case Intrinsic::fshl:
1942 case Intrinsic::fshr: {
1943 Value *Op0 = II->getArgOperand(0), *Op1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
1944 Type *Ty = II->getType();
1945 unsigned BitWidth = Ty->getScalarSizeInBits();
1946 Constant *ShAmtC;
1947 if (match(II->getArgOperand(2), m_Constant(ShAmtC)) &&
1948 !isa<ConstantExpr>(ShAmtC) && !ShAmtC->containsConstantExpression()) {
1949 // Canonicalize a shift amount constant operand to modulo the bit-width.
1950 Constant *WidthC = ConstantInt::get(Ty, BitWidth);
1951 Constant *ModuloC = ConstantExpr::getURem(ShAmtC, WidthC);
1952 if (ModuloC != ShAmtC) {
1953 II->setArgOperand(2, ModuloC);
1954 return II;
1955 }
1956 assert(ConstantExpr::getICmp(ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT, WidthC, ShAmtC) ==
1957 ConstantInt::getTrue(CmpInst::makeCmpResultType(Ty)) &&
1958 "Shift amount expected to be modulo bitwidth");
1959
1960 // Canonicalize funnel shift right by constant to funnel shift left. This
1961 // is not entirely arbitrary. For historical reasons, the backend may
1962 // recognize rotate left patterns but miss rotate right patterns.
1963 if (IID == Intrinsic::fshr) {
1964 // fshr X, Y, C --> fshl X, Y, (BitWidth - C)
1965 Constant *LeftShiftC = ConstantExpr::getSub(WidthC, ShAmtC);
1966 Module *Mod = II->getModule();
1967 Function *Fshl = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(Mod, Intrinsic::fshl, Ty);
1968 return CallInst::Create(Fshl, { Op0, Op1, LeftShiftC });
1969 }
1970 assert(IID == Intrinsic::fshl &&
1971 "All funnel shifts by simple constants should go left");
1972
1973 // fshl(X, 0, C) --> shl X, C
1974 // fshl(X, undef, C) --> shl X, C
1975 if (match(Op1, m_ZeroInt()) || match(Op1, m_Undef()))
1976 return BinaryOperator::CreateShl(Op0, ShAmtC);
1977
1978 // fshl(0, X, C) --> lshr X, (BW-C)
1979 // fshl(undef, X, C) --> lshr X, (BW-C)
1980 if (match(Op0, m_ZeroInt()) || match(Op0, m_Undef()))
1981 return BinaryOperator::CreateLShr(Op1,
1982 ConstantExpr::getSub(WidthC, ShAmtC));
1983 }
1984
1985 // Left or right might be masked.
1986 if (SimplifyDemandedInstructionBits(*II))
1987 return &CI;
1988
1989 // The shift amount (operand 2) of a funnel shift is modulo the bitwidth,
1990 // so only the low bits of the shift amount are demanded if the bitwidth is
1991 // a power-of-2.
1992 if (!isPowerOf2_32(BitWidth))
1993 break;
1994 APInt Op2Demanded = APInt::getLowBitsSet(BitWidth, Log2_32_Ceil(BitWidth));
1995 KnownBits Op2Known(BitWidth);
1996 if (SimplifyDemandedBits(II, 2, Op2Demanded, Op2Known))
1997 return &CI;
1998 break;
1999 }
2000 case Intrinsic::uadd_with_overflow:
2001 case Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow: {
2002 if (Instruction *I = canonicalizeConstantArg0ToArg1(CI))
2003 return I;
2004 if (Instruction *I = foldIntrinsicWithOverflowCommon(II))
2005 return I;
2006
2007 // Given 2 constant operands whose sum does not overflow:
2008 // uaddo (X +nuw C0), C1 -> uaddo X, C0 + C1
2009 // saddo (X +nsw C0), C1 -> saddo X, C0 + C1
2010 Value *X;
2011 const APInt *C0, *C1;
2012 Value *Arg0 = II->getArgOperand(0);
2013 Value *Arg1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
2014 bool IsSigned = IID == Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow;
2015 bool HasNWAdd = IsSigned ? match(Arg0, m_NSWAdd(m_Value(X), m_APInt(C0)))
2016 : match(Arg0, m_NUWAdd(m_Value(X), m_APInt(C0)));
2017 if (HasNWAdd && match(Arg1, m_APInt(C1))) {
2018 bool Overflow;
2019 APInt NewC =
2020 IsSigned ? C1->sadd_ov(*C0, Overflow) : C1->uadd_ov(*C0, Overflow);
2021 if (!Overflow)
2022 return replaceInstUsesWith(
2023 *II, Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(
2024 IID, X, ConstantInt::get(Arg1->getType(), NewC)));
2025 }
2026 break;
2027 }
2028
2029 case Intrinsic::umul_with_overflow:
2030 case Intrinsic::smul_with_overflow:
2031 if (Instruction *I = canonicalizeConstantArg0ToArg1(CI))
2032 return I;
2033 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2034
2035 case Intrinsic::usub_with_overflow:
2036 if (Instruction *I = foldIntrinsicWithOverflowCommon(II))
2037 return I;
2038 break;
2039
2040 case Intrinsic::ssub_with_overflow: {
2041 if (Instruction *I = foldIntrinsicWithOverflowCommon(II))
2042 return I;
2043
2044 Constant *C;
2045 Value *Arg0 = II->getArgOperand(0);
2046 Value *Arg1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
2047 // Given a constant C that is not the minimum signed value
2048 // for an integer of a given bit width:
2049 //
2050 // ssubo X, C -> saddo X, -C
2051 if (match(Arg1, m_Constant(C)) && C->isNotMinSignedValue()) {
2052 Value *NegVal = ConstantExpr::getNeg(C);
2053 // Build a saddo call that is equivalent to the discovered
2054 // ssubo call.
2055 return replaceInstUsesWith(
2056 *II, Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow,
2057 Arg0, NegVal));
2058 }
2059
2060 break;
2061 }
2062
2063 case Intrinsic::uadd_sat:
2064 case Intrinsic::sadd_sat:
2065 if (Instruction *I = canonicalizeConstantArg0ToArg1(CI))
2066 return I;
2067 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2068 case Intrinsic::usub_sat:
2069 case Intrinsic::ssub_sat: {
2070 SaturatingInst *SI = cast<SaturatingInst>(II);
2071 Type *Ty = SI->getType();
2072 Value *Arg0 = SI->getLHS();
2073 Value *Arg1 = SI->getRHS();
2074
2075 // Make use of known overflow information.
2076 OverflowResult OR = computeOverflow(SI->getBinaryOp(), SI->isSigned(),
2077 Arg0, Arg1, SI);
2078 switch (OR) {
2079 case OverflowResult::MayOverflow:
2080 break;
2081 case OverflowResult::NeverOverflows:
2082 if (SI->isSigned())
2083 return BinaryOperator::CreateNSW(SI->getBinaryOp(), Arg0, Arg1);
2084 else
2085 return BinaryOperator::CreateNUW(SI->getBinaryOp(), Arg0, Arg1);
2086 case OverflowResult::AlwaysOverflowsLow: {
2087 unsigned BitWidth = Ty->getScalarSizeInBits();
2088 APInt Min = APSInt::getMinValue(BitWidth, !SI->isSigned());
2089 return replaceInstUsesWith(*SI, ConstantInt::get(Ty, Min));
2090 }
2091 case OverflowResult::AlwaysOverflowsHigh: {
2092 unsigned BitWidth = Ty->getScalarSizeInBits();
2093 APInt Max = APSInt::getMaxValue(BitWidth, !SI->isSigned());
2094 return replaceInstUsesWith(*SI, ConstantInt::get(Ty, Max));
2095 }
2096 }
2097
2098 // ssub.sat(X, C) -> sadd.sat(X, -C) if C != MIN
2099 Constant *C;
2100 if (IID == Intrinsic::ssub_sat && match(Arg1, m_Constant(C)) &&
2101 C->isNotMinSignedValue()) {
2102 Value *NegVal = ConstantExpr::getNeg(C);
2103 return replaceInstUsesWith(
2104 *II, Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(
2105 Intrinsic::sadd_sat, Arg0, NegVal));
2106 }
2107
2108 // sat(sat(X + Val2) + Val) -> sat(X + (Val+Val2))
2109 // sat(sat(X - Val2) - Val) -> sat(X - (Val+Val2))
2110 // if Val and Val2 have the same sign
2111 if (auto *Other = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(Arg0)) {
2112 Value *X;
2113 const APInt *Val, *Val2;
2114 APInt NewVal;
2115 bool IsUnsigned =
2116 IID == Intrinsic::uadd_sat || IID == Intrinsic::usub_sat;
2117 if (Other->getIntrinsicID() == IID &&
2118 match(Arg1, m_APInt(Val)) &&
2119 match(Other->getArgOperand(0), m_Value(X)) &&
2120 match(Other->getArgOperand(1), m_APInt(Val2))) {
2121 if (IsUnsigned)
2122 NewVal = Val->uadd_sat(*Val2);
2123 else if (Val->isNonNegative() == Val2->isNonNegative()) {
2124 bool Overflow;
2125 NewVal = Val->sadd_ov(*Val2, Overflow);
2126 if (Overflow) {
2127 // Both adds together may add more than SignedMaxValue
2128 // without saturating the final result.
2129 break;
2130 }
2131 } else {
2132 // Cannot fold saturated addition with different signs.
2133 break;
2134 }
2135
2136 return replaceInstUsesWith(
2137 *II, Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(
2138 IID, X, ConstantInt::get(II->getType(), NewVal)));
2139 }
2140 }
2141 break;
2142 }
2143
2144 case Intrinsic::minnum:
2145 case Intrinsic::maxnum:
2146 case Intrinsic::minimum:
2147 case Intrinsic::maximum: {
2148 if (Instruction *I = canonicalizeConstantArg0ToArg1(CI))
2149 return I;
2150 Value *Arg0 = II->getArgOperand(0);
2151 Value *Arg1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
2152 Value *X, *Y;
2153 if (match(Arg0, m_FNeg(m_Value(X))) && match(Arg1, m_FNeg(m_Value(Y))) &&
2154 (Arg0->hasOneUse() || Arg1->hasOneUse())) {
2155 // If both operands are negated, invert the call and negate the result:
2156 // min(-X, -Y) --> -(max(X, Y))
2157 // max(-X, -Y) --> -(min(X, Y))
2158 Intrinsic::ID NewIID;
2159 switch (IID) {
2160 case Intrinsic::maxnum:
2161 NewIID = Intrinsic::minnum;
2162 break;
2163 case Intrinsic::minnum:
2164 NewIID = Intrinsic::maxnum;
2165 break;
2166 case Intrinsic::maximum:
2167 NewIID = Intrinsic::minimum;
2168 break;
2169 case Intrinsic::minimum:
2170 NewIID = Intrinsic::maximum;
2171 break;
2172 default:
2173 llvm_unreachable("unexpected intrinsic ID");
2174 }
2175 Value *NewCall = Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(NewIID, X, Y, II);
2176 Instruction *FNeg = BinaryOperator::CreateFNeg(NewCall);
2177 FNeg->copyIRFlags(II);
2178 return FNeg;
2179 }
2180
2181 // m(m(X, C2), C1) -> m(X, C)
2182 const APFloat *C1, *C2;
2183 if (auto *M = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(Arg0)) {
2184 if (M->getIntrinsicID() == IID && match(Arg1, m_APFloat(C1)) &&
2185 ((match(M->getArgOperand(0), m_Value(X)) &&
2186 match(M->getArgOperand(1), m_APFloat(C2))) ||
2187 (match(M->getArgOperand(1), m_Value(X)) &&
2188 match(M->getArgOperand(0), m_APFloat(C2))))) {
2189 APFloat Res(0.0);
2190 switch (IID) {
2191 case Intrinsic::maxnum:
2192 Res = maxnum(*C1, *C2);
2193 break;
2194 case Intrinsic::minnum:
2195 Res = minnum(*C1, *C2);
2196 break;
2197 case Intrinsic::maximum:
2198 Res = maximum(*C1, *C2);
2199 break;
2200 case Intrinsic::minimum:
2201 Res = minimum(*C1, *C2);
2202 break;
2203 default:
2204 llvm_unreachable("unexpected intrinsic ID");
2205 }
2206 Instruction *NewCall = Builder.CreateBinaryIntrinsic(
2207 IID, X, ConstantFP::get(Arg0->getType(), Res));
2208 NewCall->copyIRFlags(II);
2209 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, NewCall);
2210 }
2211 }
2212
2213 break;
2214 }
2215 case Intrinsic::fmuladd: {
2216 // Canonicalize fast fmuladd to the separate fmul + fadd.
2217 if (II->isFast()) {
2218 BuilderTy::FastMathFlagGuard Guard(Builder);
2219 Builder.setFastMathFlags(II->getFastMathFlags());
2220 Value *Mul = Builder.CreateFMul(II->getArgOperand(0),
2221 II->getArgOperand(1));
2222 Value *Add = Builder.CreateFAdd(Mul, II->getArgOperand(2));
2223 Add->takeName(II);
2224 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, Add);
2225 }
2226
2227 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2228 }
2229 case Intrinsic::fma: {
2230 if (Instruction *I = canonicalizeConstantArg0ToArg1(CI))
2231 return I;
2232
2233 // fma fneg(x), fneg(y), z -> fma x, y, z
2234 Value *Src0 = II->getArgOperand(0);
2235 Value *Src1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
2236 Value *X, *Y;
2237 if (match(Src0, m_FNeg(m_Value(X))) && match(Src1, m_FNeg(m_Value(Y)))) {
2238 II->setArgOperand(0, X);
2239 II->setArgOperand(1, Y);
2240 return II;
2241 }
2242
2243 // fma fabs(x), fabs(x), z -> fma x, x, z
2244 if (match(Src0, m_FAbs(m_Value(X))) &&
2245 match(Src1, m_FAbs(m_Specific(X)))) {
2246 II->setArgOperand(0, X);
2247 II->setArgOperand(1, X);
2248 return II;
2249 }
2250
2251 // fma x, 1, z -> fadd x, z
2252 if (match(Src1, m_FPOne())) {
2253 auto *FAdd = BinaryOperator::CreateFAdd(Src0, II->getArgOperand(2));
2254 FAdd->copyFastMathFlags(II);
2255 return FAdd;
2256 }
2257
2258 break;
2259 }
2260 case Intrinsic::fabs: {
2261 Value *Cond;
2262 Constant *LHS, *RHS;
2263 if (match(II->getArgOperand(0),
2264 m_Select(m_Value(Cond), m_Constant(LHS), m_Constant(RHS)))) {
2265 CallInst *Call0 = Builder.CreateCall(II->getCalledFunction(), {LHS});
2266 CallInst *Call1 = Builder.CreateCall(II->getCalledFunction(), {RHS});
2267 return SelectInst::Create(Cond, Call0, Call1);
2268 }
2269
2270 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2271 }
2272 case Intrinsic::ceil:
2273 case Intrinsic::floor:
2274 case Intrinsic::round:
2275 case Intrinsic::nearbyint:
2276 case Intrinsic::rint:
2277 case Intrinsic::trunc: {

2576 // Folding cmp(sub(a,b),0) -> cmp(a,b) and cmp(0,sub(a,b)) -> cmp(b,a)
2577 Value *Arg0 = II->getArgOperand(0);
2578 Value *Arg1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
2579 bool Arg0IsZero = match(Arg0, m_PosZeroFP());

3150 if (!Elt || !(isa<ConstantInt>(Elt) || isa<UndefValue>(Elt))) {
3151 AllEltsOk = false;

3281 if (match(KeyArg, m_ZeroInt()) &&
3282 match(DataArg, m_Xor(m_Value(Data), m_Value(Key)))) {
3283 II->setArgOperand(0, Data);
3284 II->setArgOperand(1, Key);
3285 return II;
3286 }
3287 break;
3288 }
3289 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_rcp: {
3290 Value *Src = II->getArgOperand(0);
3291
3292 // TODO: Move to ConstantFolding/InstSimplify?
3293 if (isa<UndefValue>(Src))
3294 return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, Src);
3295
3296 if (const ConstantFP *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Src)) {
3297 const APFloat &ArgVal = C->getValueAPF();
3298 APFloat Val(ArgVal.getSemantics(), 1.0);
3299 APFloat::opStatus Status = Val.divide(ArgVal,
3300 APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
3301 // Only do this if it was exact and therefore not dependent on the
3302 // rounding mode.
3303 if (Status == APFloat::opOK)
3304 return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, ConstantFP::get(II->getContext(), Val));
3305 }
3306
3307 break;
3308 }
3309 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_rsq: {
3310 Value *Src = II->getArgOperand(0);
3311
3312 // TODO: Move to ConstantFolding/InstSimplify?
3313 if (isa<UndefValue>(Src))
3314 return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, Src);
3315 break;
3316 }
3317 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_frexp_mant:
3318 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_frexp_exp: {
3319 Value *Src = II->getArgOperand(0);
3320 if (const ConstantFP *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Src)) {
3321 int Exp;
3322 APFloat Significand = frexp(C->getValueAPF(), Exp,
3323 APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
3324
3325 if (IID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_frexp_mant) {
3326 return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, ConstantFP::get(II->getContext(),
3327 Significand));
3328 }
3329
3330 // Match instruction special case behavior.
3331 if (Exp == APFloat::IEK_NaN || Exp == APFloat::IEK_Inf)
3332 Exp = 0;
3333
3334 return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, ConstantInt::get(II->getType(), Exp));
3335 }
3336
3337 if (isa<UndefValue>(Src))
3338 return replaceInstUsesWith(CI, UndefValue::get(II->getType()));
3339
3340 break;
3341 }
3342 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_class: {
3343 enum {
3344 S_NAN = 1 << 0, // Signaling NaN
3345 Q_NAN = 1 << 1, // Quiet NaN
3346 N_INFINITY = 1 << 2, // Negative infinity
3347 N_NORMAL = 1 << 3, // Negative normal
3348 N_SUBNORMAL = 1 << 4, // Negative subnormal
3349 N_ZERO = 1 << 5, // Negative zero
3350 P_ZERO = 1 << 6, // Positive zero
3351 P_SUBNORMAL = 1 << 7, // Positive subnormal
3352 P_NORMAL = 1 << 8, // Positive normal
3353 P_INFINITY = 1 << 9 // Positive infinity
3354 };
3355
3356 const uint32_t FullMask = S_NAN | Q_NAN | N_INFINITY | N_NORMAL |
3357 N_SUBNORMAL | N_ZERO | P_ZERO | P_SUBNORMAL | P_NORMAL | P_INFINITY;
3358
3359 Value *Src0 = II->getArgOperand(0);
3360 Value *Src1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
3361 const ConstantInt *CMask = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Src1);
3362 if (!CMask) {
3363 if (isa<UndefValue>(Src0))
3364 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, UndefValue::get(II->getType()));
3365
3366 if (isa<UndefValue>(Src1))
3367 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, ConstantInt::get(II->getType(), false));
3368 break;
3369 }
3370
3371 uint32_t Mask = CMask->getZExtValue();
3372
3373 // If all tests are made, it doesn't matter what the value is.
3374 if ((Mask & FullMask) == FullMask)
3375 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, ConstantInt::get(II->getType(), true));
3376
3377 if ((Mask & FullMask) == 0)
3378 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, ConstantInt::get(II->getType(), false));
3379
3380 if (Mask == (S_NAN | Q_NAN)) {
3381 // Equivalent of isnan. Replace with standard fcmp.
3382 Value *FCmp = Builder.CreateFCmpUNO(Src0, Src0);
3383 FCmp->takeName(II);
3384 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, FCmp);
3385 }
3386
3387 if (Mask == (N_ZERO | P_ZERO)) {
3388 // Equivalent of == 0.
3389 Value *FCmp = Builder.CreateFCmpOEQ(
3390 Src0, ConstantFP::get(Src0->getType(), 0.0));
3391
3392 FCmp->takeName(II);
3393 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, FCmp);
3394 }
3395
3396 // fp_class (nnan x), qnan|snan|other -> fp_class (nnan x), other
3397 if (((Mask & S_NAN) || (Mask & Q_NAN)) && isKnownNeverNaN(Src0, &TLI)) {
3398 II->setArgOperand(1, ConstantInt::get(Src1->getType(),
3399 Mask & ~(S_NAN | Q_NAN)));
3400 return II;
3401 }
3402
3403 const ConstantFP *CVal = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Src0);
3404 if (!CVal) {
3405 if (isa<UndefValue>(Src0))
3406 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, UndefValue::get(II->getType()));
3407
3408 // Clamp mask to used bits
3409 if ((Mask & FullMask) != Mask) {
3410 CallInst *NewCall = Builder.CreateCall(II->getCalledFunction(),
3411 { Src0, ConstantInt::get(Src1->getType(), Mask & FullMask) }
3412 );
3413
3414 NewCall->takeName(II);
3415 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, NewCall);
3416 }
3417
3418 break;
3419 }
3420
3421 const APFloat &Val = CVal->getValueAPF();
3422
3423 bool Result =
3424 ((Mask & S_NAN) && Val.isNaN() && Val.isSignaling()) ||
3425 ((Mask & Q_NAN) && Val.isNaN() && !Val.isSignaling()) ||
3426 ((Mask & N_INFINITY) && Val.isInfinity() && Val.isNegative()) ||
3427 ((Mask & N_NORMAL) && Val.isNormal() && Val.isNegative()) ||
3428 ((Mask & N_SUBNORMAL) && Val.isDenormal() && Val.isNegative()) ||
3429 ((Mask & N_ZERO) && Val.isZero() && Val.isNegative()) ||
3430 ((Mask & P_ZERO) && Val.isZero() && !Val.isNegative()) ||
3431 ((Mask & P_SUBNORMAL) && Val.isDenormal() && !Val.isNegative()) ||
3432 ((Mask & P_NORMAL) && Val.isNormal() && !Val.isNegative()) ||
3433 ((Mask & P_INFINITY) && Val.isInfinity() && !Val.isNegative());
3434
3435 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, ConstantInt::get(II->getType(), Result));
3436 }
3437 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cvt_pkrtz: {
3438 Value *Src0 = II->getArgOperand(0);
3439 Value *Src1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
3440 if (const ConstantFP *C0 = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Src0)) {
3441 if (const ConstantFP *C1 = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Src1)) {
3442 const fltSemantics &HalfSem
3443 = II->getType()->getScalarType()->getFltSemantics();
3444 bool LosesInfo;
3445 APFloat Val0 = C0->getValueAPF();
3446 APFloat Val1 = C1->getValueAPF();
3447 Val0.convert(HalfSem, APFloat::rmTowardZero, &LosesInfo);
3448 Val1.convert(HalfSem, APFloat::rmTowardZero, &LosesInfo);
3449
3450 Constant *Folded = ConstantVector::get({
3451 ConstantFP::get(II->getContext(), Val0),
3452 ConstantFP::get(II->getContext(), Val1) });
3453 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, Folded);
3454 }
3455 }
3456
3457 if (isa<UndefValue>(Src0) && isa<UndefValue>(Src1))
3458 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, UndefValue::get(II->getType()));
3459
3460 break;
3461 }
3462 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cvt_pknorm_i16:
3463 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cvt_pknorm_u16:
3464 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cvt_pk_i16:
3465 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cvt_pk_u16: {
3466 Value *Src0 = II->getArgOperand(0);
3467 Value *Src1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
3468
3469 if (isa<UndefValue>(Src0) && isa<UndefValue>(Src1))
3470 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, UndefValue::get(II->getType()));
3471
3472 break;
3473 }
3474 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_ubfe:
3475 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_sbfe: {
3476 // Decompose simple cases into standard shifts.
3477 Value *Src = II->getArgOperand(0);
3478 if (isa<UndefValue>(Src))
3479 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, Src);
3480
3481 unsigned Width;
3482 Type *Ty = II->getType();
3483 unsigned IntSize = Ty->getIntegerBitWidth();
3484
3485 ConstantInt *CWidth = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(II->getArgOperand(2));
3486 if (CWidth) {
3487 Width = CWidth->getZExtValue();
3488 if ((Width & (IntSize - 1)) == 0)
3489 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, ConstantInt::getNullValue(Ty));
3490
3491 if (Width >= IntSize) {
3492 // Hardware ignores high bits, so remove those.
3493 II->setArgOperand(2, ConstantInt::get(CWidth->getType(),
3494 Width & (IntSize - 1)));
3495 return II;
3496 }
3497 }
3498
3499 unsigned Offset;
3500 ConstantInt *COffset = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(II->getArgOperand(1));
3501 if (COffset) {
3502 Offset = COffset->getZExtValue();
3503 if (Offset >= IntSize) {
3504 II->setArgOperand(1, ConstantInt::get(COffset->getType(),
3505 Offset & (IntSize - 1)));
3506 return II;
3507 }
3508 }
3509
3510 bool Signed = IID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_sbfe;
3511
3512 if (!CWidth || !COffset)
3513 break;
3514
3515 // The case of Width == 0 is handled above, which makes this tranformation
3516 // safe. If Width == 0, then the ashr and lshr instructions become poison
3517 // value since the shift amount would be equal to the bit size.
3518 assert(Width != 0);
3519
3520 // TODO: This allows folding to undef when the hardware has specific
3521 // behavior?
3522 if (Offset + Width < IntSize) {
3523 Value *Shl = Builder.CreateShl(Src, IntSize - Offset - Width);
3524 Value *RightShift = Signed ? Builder.CreateAShr(Shl, IntSize - Width)
3525 : Builder.CreateLShr(Shl, IntSize - Width);
3526 RightShift->takeName(II);
3527 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, RightShift);
3528 }
3529
3530 Value *RightShift = Signed ? Builder.CreateAShr(Src, Offset)
3531 : Builder.CreateLShr(Src, Offset);
3532
3533 RightShift->takeName(II);
3534 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, RightShift);
3535 }
3536 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_exp:
3537 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_exp_compr: {
3538 ConstantInt *En = cast<ConstantInt>(II->getArgOperand(1));
3539 unsigned EnBits = En->getZExtValue();
3540 if (EnBits == 0xf)
3541 break; // All inputs enabled.
3542
3543 bool IsCompr = IID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_exp_compr;
3544 bool Changed = false;
3545 for (int I = 0; I < (IsCompr ? 2 : 4); ++I) {
3546 if ((!IsCompr && (EnBits & (1 << I)) == 0) ||
3547 (IsCompr && ((EnBits & (0x3 << (2 * I))) == 0))) {
3548 Value *Src = II->getArgOperand(I + 2);
3549 if (!isa<UndefValue>(Src)) {
3550 II->setArgOperand(I + 2, UndefValue::get(Src->getType()));
3551 Changed = true;
3552 }
3553 }
3554 }
3555
3556 if (Changed)
3557 return II;
3558
3559 break;
3560 }
3561 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_fmed3: {
3562 // Note this does not preserve proper sNaN behavior if IEEE-mode is enabled
3563 // for the shader.
3564
3565 Value *Src0 = II->getArgOperand(0);
3566 Value *Src1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
3567 Value *Src2 = II->getArgOperand(2);
3568
3569 // Checking for NaN before canonicalization provides better fidelity when
3570 // mapping other operations onto fmed3 since the order of operands is
3571 // unchanged.
3572 CallInst *NewCall = nullptr;
3573 if (match(Src0, m_NaN()) || isa<UndefValue>(Src0)) {
3574 NewCall = Builder.CreateMinNum(Src1, Src2);
3575 } else if (match(Src1, m_NaN()) || isa<UndefValue>(Src1)) {
3576 NewCall = Builder.CreateMinNum(Src0, Src2);
3577 } else if (match(Src2, m_NaN()) || isa<UndefValue>(Src2)) {
3578 NewCall = Builder.CreateMaxNum(Src0, Src1);
3579 }
3580
3581 if (NewCall) {
3582 NewCall->copyFastMathFlags(II);
3583 NewCall->takeName(II);
3584 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, NewCall);
3585 }
3586
3587 bool Swap = false;
3588 // Canonicalize constants to RHS operands.
3589 //
3590 // fmed3(c0, x, c1) -> fmed3(x, c0, c1)
3591 if (isa<Constant>(Src0) && !isa<Constant>(Src1)) {
3592 std::swap(Src0, Src1);
3593 Swap = true;
3594 }
3595
3596 if (isa<Constant>(Src1) && !isa<Constant>(Src2)) {
3597 std::swap(Src1, Src2);
3598 Swap = true;
3599 }
3600
3601 if (isa<Constant>(Src0) && !isa<Constant>(Src1)) {
3602 std::swap(Src0, Src1);
3603 Swap = true;
3604 }
3605
3606 if (Swap) {
3607 II->setArgOperand(0, Src0);
3608 II->setArgOperand(1, Src1);
3609 II->setArgOperand(2, Src2);
3610 return II;
3611 }
3612
3613 if (const ConstantFP *C0 = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Src0)) {
3614 if (const ConstantFP *C1 = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Src1)) {
3615 if (const ConstantFP *C2 = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Src2)) {
3616 APFloat Result = fmed3AMDGCN(C0->getValueAPF(), C1->getValueAPF(),
3617 C2->getValueAPF());
3618 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II,
3619 ConstantFP::get(Builder.getContext(), Result));
3620 }
3621 }
3622 }
3623
3624 break;
3625 }
3626 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_icmp:
3627 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_fcmp: {
3628 const ConstantInt *CC = cast<ConstantInt>(II->getArgOperand(2));
3629 // Guard against invalid arguments.
3630 int64_t CCVal = CC->getZExtValue();
3631 bool IsInteger = IID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_icmp;
3632 if ((IsInteger && (CCVal < CmpInst::FIRST_ICMP_PREDICATE ||
3633 CCVal > CmpInst::LAST_ICMP_PREDICATE)) ||
3634 (!IsInteger && (CCVal < CmpInst::FIRST_FCMP_PREDICATE ||
3635 CCVal > CmpInst::LAST_FCMP_PREDICATE)))
3636 break;
3637
3638 Value *Src0 = II->getArgOperand(0);
3639 Value *Src1 = II->getArgOperand(1);
3640
3641 if (auto *CSrc0 = dyn_cast<Constant>(Src0)) {
3642 if (auto *CSrc1 = dyn_cast<Constant>(Src1)) {
3643 Constant *CCmp = ConstantExpr::getCompare(CCVal, CSrc0, CSrc1);
3644 if (CCmp->isNullValue()) {
3645 return replaceInstUsesWith(
3646 *II, ConstantExpr::getSExt(CCmp, II->getType()));
3647 }
3648
3649 // The result of V_ICMP/V_FCMP assembly instructions (which this
3650 // intrinsic exposes) is one bit per thread, masked with the EXEC
3651 // register (which contains the bitmask of live threads). So a
3652 // comparison that always returns true is the same as a read of the
3653 // EXEC register.
3654 Function *NewF = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(
3655 II->getModule(), Intrinsic::read_register, II->getType());
3656 Metadata *MDArgs[] = {MDString::get(II->getContext(), "exec")};
3657 MDNode *MD = MDNode::get(II->getContext(), MDArgs);
3658 Value *Args[] = {MetadataAsValue::get(II->getContext(), MD)};
3659 CallInst *NewCall = Builder.CreateCall(NewF, Args);
3660 NewCall->addAttribute(AttributeList::FunctionIndex,
3661 Attribute::Convergent);
3662 NewCall->takeName(II);
3663 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, NewCall);
3664 }
3665
3666 // Canonicalize constants to RHS.
3667 CmpInst::Predicate SwapPred
3668 = CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(static_cast<CmpInst::Predicate>(CCVal));
3669 II->setArgOperand(0, Src1);
3670 II->setArgOperand(1, Src0);
3671 II->setArgOperand(2, ConstantInt::get(CC->getType(),
3672 static_cast<int>(SwapPred)));
3673 return II;
3674 }
3675
3676 if (CCVal != CmpInst::ICMP_EQ && CCVal != CmpInst::ICMP_NE)
3677 break;
3678
3679 // Canonicalize compare eq with true value to compare != 0
3680 // llvm.amdgcn.icmp(zext (i1 x), 1, eq)
3681 // -> llvm.amdgcn.icmp(zext (i1 x), 0, ne)
3682 // llvm.amdgcn.icmp(sext (i1 x), -1, eq)
3683 // -> llvm.amdgcn.icmp(sext (i1 x), 0, ne)
3684 Value *ExtSrc;
3685 if (CCVal == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ &&
3686 ((match(Src1, m_One()) && match(Src0, m_ZExt(m_Value(ExtSrc)))) ||
3687 (match(Src1, m_AllOnes()) && match(Src0, m_SExt(m_Value(ExtSrc))))) &&
3688 ExtSrc->getType()->isIntegerTy(1)) {
3689 II->setArgOperand(1, ConstantInt::getNullValue(Src1->getType()));
3690 II->setArgOperand(2, ConstantInt::get(CC->getType(), CmpInst::ICMP_NE));
3691 return II;
3692 }
3693
3694 CmpInst::Predicate SrcPred;
3695 Value *SrcLHS;
3696 Value *SrcRHS;
3697
3698 // Fold compare eq/ne with 0 from a compare result as the predicate to the
3699 // intrinsic. The typical use is a wave vote function in the library, which
3700 // will be fed from a user code condition compared with 0. Fold in the
3701 // redundant compare.
3702
3703 // llvm.amdgcn.icmp([sz]ext ([if]cmp pred a, b), 0, ne)
3704 // -> llvm.amdgcn.[if]cmp(a, b, pred)
3705 //
3706 // llvm.amdgcn.icmp([sz]ext ([if]cmp pred a, b), 0, eq)
3707 // -> llvm.amdgcn.[if]cmp(a, b, inv pred)
3708 if (match(Src1, m_Zero()) &&
3709 match(Src0,
3710 m_ZExtOrSExt(m_Cmp(SrcPred, m_Value(SrcLHS), m_Value(SrcRHS))))) {
3711 if (CCVal == CmpInst::ICMP_EQ)
3712 SrcPred = CmpInst::getInversePredicate(SrcPred);
3713
3714 Intrinsic::ID NewIID = CmpInst::isFPPredicate(SrcPred) ?
3715 Intrinsic::amdgcn_fcmp : Intrinsic::amdgcn_icmp;
3716
3717 Type *Ty = SrcLHS->getType();
3718 if (auto *CmpType = dyn_cast<IntegerType>(Ty)) {
3719 // Promote to next legal integer type.
3720 unsigned Width = CmpType->getBitWidth();
3721 unsigned NewWidth = Width;
3722
3723 // Don't do anything for i1 comparisons.
3724 if (Width == 1)
3725 break;
3726
3727 if (Width <= 16)
3728 NewWidth = 16;
3729 else if (Width <= 32)
3730 NewWidth = 32;
3731 else if (Width <= 64)
3732 NewWidth = 64;
3733 else if (Width > 64)
3734 break; // Can't handle this.
3735
3736 if (Width != NewWidth) {
3737 IntegerType *CmpTy = Builder.getIntNTy(NewWidth);
3738 if (CmpInst::isSigned(SrcPred)) {
3739 SrcLHS = Builder.CreateSExt(SrcLHS, CmpTy);
3740 SrcRHS = Builder.CreateSExt(SrcRHS, CmpTy);
3741 } else {
3742 SrcLHS = Builder.CreateZExt(SrcLHS, CmpTy);
3743 SrcRHS = Builder.CreateZExt(SrcRHS, CmpTy);
3744 }
3745 }
3746 } else if (!Ty->isFloatTy() && !Ty->isDoubleTy() && !Ty->isHalfTy())
3747 break;
3748
3749 Function *NewF =
3750 Intrinsic::getDeclaration(II->getModule(), NewIID, SrcLHS->getType());
3751 Value *Args[] = { SrcLHS, SrcRHS,
3752 ConstantInt::get(CC->getType(), SrcPred) };
3753 CallInst *NewCall = Builder.CreateCall(NewF, Args);
3754 NewCall->takeName(II);
3755 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, NewCall);
3756 }
3757
3758 break;
3759 }
3760 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_wqm_vote: {
3761 // wqm_vote is identity when the argument is constant.
3762 if (!isa<Constant>(II->getArgOperand(0)))
3763 break;
3764
3765 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, II->getArgOperand(0));
3766 }
3767 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_kill: {
3768 const ConstantInt *C = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(II->getArgOperand(0));
3769 if (!C || !C->getZExtValue())
3770 break;
3771
3772 // amdgcn.kill(i1 1) is a no-op
3773 return eraseInstFromFunction(CI);
3774 }
3775 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_update_dpp: {
3776 Value *Old = II->getArgOperand(0);
3777
3778 auto BC = cast<ConstantInt>(II->getArgOperand(5));
3779 auto RM = cast<ConstantInt>(II->getArgOperand(3));
3780 auto BM = cast<ConstantInt>(II->getArgOperand(4));
3781 if (BC->isZeroValue() ||
3782 RM->getZExtValue() != 0xF ||
3783 BM->getZExtValue() != 0xF ||
3784 isa<UndefValue>(Old))
3785 break;
3786
3787 // If bound_ctrl = 1, row mask = bank mask = 0xf we can omit old value.
3788 II->setOperand(0, UndefValue::get(Old->getType()));
3789 return II;
3790 }
3791 case Intrinsic::stackrestore: {
3792 // If the save is right next to the restore, remove the restore. This can
3793 // happen when variable allocas are DCE'd.
3794 if (IntrinsicInst *SS = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(II->getArgOperand(0))) {
3795 if (SS->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::stacksave) {
3796 // Skip over debug info.
3797 if (SS->getNextNonDebugInstruction() == II) {
3798 return eraseInstFromFunction(CI);
3799 }
3800 }
3801 }
3802
3803 // Scan down this block to see if there is another stack restore in the
3804 // same block without an intervening call/alloca.
3805 BasicBlock::iterator BI(II);
3806 Instruction *TI = II->getParent()->getTerminator();
3807 bool CannotRemove = false;
3808 for (++BI; &*BI != TI; ++BI) {
3809 if (isa<AllocaInst>(BI)) {
3810 CannotRemove = true;
3811 break;
3812 }
3813 if (CallInst *BCI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(BI)) {
3814 if (auto *II2 = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(BCI)) {
3815 // If there is a stackrestore below this one, remove this one.
3816 if (II2->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::stackrestore)
3817 return eraseInstFromFunction(CI);
3818
3819 // Bail if we cross over an intrinsic with side effects, such as
3820 // llvm.stacksave, llvm.read_register, or llvm.setjmp.
3821 if (II2->mayHaveSideEffects()) {
3822 CannotRemove = true;
3823 break;
3824 }
3825 } else {
3826 // If we found a non-intrinsic call, we can't remove the stack
3827 // restore.
3828 CannotRemove = true;
3829 break;
3830 }
3831 }
3832 }
3833
3834 // If the stack restore is in a return, resume, or unwind block and if there
3835 // are no allocas or calls between the restore and the return, nuke the
3836 // restore.
3837 if (!CannotRemove && (isa<ReturnInst>(TI) || isa<ResumeInst>(TI)))
3838 return eraseInstFromFunction(CI);
3839 break;
3840 }
3841 case Intrinsic::lifetime_start:
3842 // Asan needs to poison memory to detect invalid access which is possible
3843 // even for empty lifetime range.
3844 if (II->getFunction()->hasFnAttribute(Attribute::SanitizeAddress) ||
3845 II->getFunction()->hasFnAttribute(Attribute::SanitizeHWAddress))
3846 break;
3847
3848 if (removeTriviallyEmptyRange(*II, Intrinsic::lifetime_start,
3849 Intrinsic::lifetime_end, *this))
3850 return nullptr;
3851 break;
3852 case Intrinsic::assume: {
3853 Value *IIOperand = II->getArgOperand(0);
3854 // Remove an assume if it is followed by an identical assume.
3855 // TODO: Do we need this? Unless there are conflicting assumptions, the
3856 // computeKnownBits(IIOperand) below here eliminates redundant assumes.
3857 Instruction *Next = II->getNextNonDebugInstruction();
3858 if (match(Next, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::assume>(m_Specific(IIOperand))))
3859 return eraseInstFromFunction(CI);
3860
3861 // Canonicalize assume(a && b) -> assume(a); assume(b);
3862 // Note: New assumption intrinsics created here are registered by
3863 // the InstCombineIRInserter object.
3864 FunctionType *AssumeIntrinsicTy = II->getFunctionType();
3865 Value *AssumeIntrinsic = II->getCalledValue();
3866 Value *A, *B;
3867 if (match(IIOperand, m_And(m_Value(A), m_Value(B)))) {
3868 Builder.CreateCall(AssumeIntrinsicTy, AssumeIntrinsic, A, II->getName());
3869 Builder.CreateCall(AssumeIntrinsicTy, AssumeIntrinsic, B, II->getName());
3870 return eraseInstFromFunction(*II);
3871 }
3872 // assume(!(a || b)) -> assume(!a); assume(!b);
3873 if (match(IIOperand, m_Not(m_Or(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))))) {
3874 Builder.CreateCall(AssumeIntrinsicTy, AssumeIntrinsic,
3875 Builder.CreateNot(A), II->getName());
3876 Builder.CreateCall(AssumeIntrinsicTy, AssumeIntrinsic,
3877 Builder.CreateNot(B), II->getName());
3878 return eraseInstFromFunction(*II);
3879 }
3880
3881 // assume( (load addr) != null ) -> add 'nonnull' metadata to load
3882 // (if assume is valid at the load)
3883 CmpInst::Predicate Pred;
3884 Instruction *LHS;
3885 if (match(IIOperand, m_ICmp(Pred, m_Instruction(LHS), m_Zero())) &&
3886 Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_NE && LHS->getOpcode() == Instruction::Load &&
3887 LHS->getType()->isPointerTy() &&
3888 isValidAssumeForContext(II, LHS, &DT)) {
3889 MDNode *MD = MDNode::get(II->getContext(), None);
3890 LHS->setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_nonnull, MD);
3891 return eraseInstFromFunction(*II);
3892
3893 // TODO: apply nonnull return attributes to calls and invokes
3894 // TODO: apply range metadata for range check patterns?
3895 }
3896
3897 // If there is a dominating assume with the same condition as this one,
3898 // then this one is redundant, and should be removed.
3899 KnownBits Known(1);
3900 computeKnownBits(IIOperand, Known, 0, II);
3901 if (Known.isAllOnes())
3902 return eraseInstFromFunction(*II);
3903
3904 // Update the cache of affected values for this assumption (we might be
3905 // here because we just simplified the condition).
3906 AC.updateAffectedValues(II);
3907 break;
3908 }
3909 case Intrinsic::experimental_gc_relocate: {
3910 // Translate facts known about a pointer before relocating into
3911 // facts about the relocate value, while being careful to
3912 // preserve relocation semantics.
3913 Value *DerivedPtr = cast<GCRelocateInst>(II)->getDerivedPtr();
3914
3915 // Remove the relocation if unused, note that this check is required
3916 // to prevent the cases below from looping forever.
3917 if (II->use_empty())
3918 return eraseInstFromFunction(*II);
3919
3920 // Undef is undef, even after relocation.
3921 // TODO: provide a hook for this in GCStrategy. This is clearly legal for
3922 // most practical collectors, but there was discussion in the review thread
3923 // about whether it was legal for all possible collectors.
3924 if (isa<UndefValue>(DerivedPtr))
3925 // Use undef of gc_relocate's type to replace it.
3926 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, UndefValue::get(II->getType()));
3927
3928 if (auto *PT = dyn_cast<PointerType>(II->getType())) {
3929 // The relocation of null will be null for most any collector.
3930 // TODO: provide a hook for this in GCStrategy. There might be some
3931 // weird collector this property does not hold for.
3932 if (isa<ConstantPointerNull>(DerivedPtr))
3933 // Use null-pointer of gc_relocate's type to replace it.
3934 return replaceInstUsesWith(*II, ConstantPointerNull::get(PT));
3935
3936 // isKnownNonNull -> nonnull attribute
3937 if (!II->hasRetAttr(Attribute::NonNull) &&
3938 isKnownNonZero(DerivedPtr, DL, 0, &AC, II, &DT)) {
3939 II->addAttribute(AttributeList::ReturnIndex, Attribute::NonNull);
3940 return II;
3941 }
3942 }
3943
3944 // TODO: bitcast(relocate(p)) -> relocate(bitcast(p))
3945 // Canonicalize on the type from the uses to the defs
3946
3947 // TODO: relocate((gep p, C, C2, ...)) -> gep(relocate(p), C, C2, ...)
3948 break;
3949 }
3950
3951 case Intrinsic::experimental_guard: {
3952 // Is this guard followed by another guard? We scan forward over a small
3953 // fixed window of instructions to handle common cases with conditions
3954 // computed between guards.
3955 Instruction *NextInst = II->getNextNode();
3956 for (unsigned i = 0; i < GuardWideningWindow; i++) {
3957 // Note: Using context-free form to avoid compile time blow up
3958 if (!isSafeToSpeculativelyExecute(NextInst))
3959 break;
3960 NextInst = NextInst->getNextNode();
3961 }
3962 Value *NextCond = nullptr;
3963 if (match(NextInst,
3964 m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::experimental_guard>(m_Value(NextCond)))) {
3965 Value *CurrCond = II->getArgOperand(0);
3966
3967 // Remove a guard that it is immediately preceded by an identical guard.
3968 if (CurrCond == NextCond)
3969 return eraseInstFromFunction(*NextInst);
3970
3971 // Otherwise canonicalize guard(a); guard(b) -> guard(a & b).
3972 Instruction* MoveI = II->getNextNode();
3973 while (MoveI != NextInst) {
3974 auto *Temp = MoveI;
3975 MoveI = MoveI->getNextNode();
3976 Temp->moveBefore(II);
3977 }
3978 II->setArgOperand(0, Builder.CreateAnd(CurrCond, NextCond));
3979 return eraseInstFromFunction(*NextInst);
3980 }
3981 break;
3982 }
3983 }
3984 return visitCallBase(*II);
3985}

3987// Fence instruction simplification
3988Instruction *InstCombiner::visitFenceInst(FenceInst &FI) {
3989 // Remove identical consecutive fences.
3990 Instruction *Next = FI.getNextNonDebugInstruction();
3991 if (auto *NFI = dyn_cast<FenceInst>(Next))
3992 if (FI.isIdenticalTo(NFI))
3993 return eraseInstFromFunction(FI);
3994 return nullptr;
3995}

3997// InvokeInst simplification
3998Instruction *InstCombiner::visitInvokeInst(InvokeInst &II) {
3999 return visitCallBase(II);
4000}

4002// CallBrInst simplification
4003Instruction *InstCombiner::visitCallBrInst(CallBrInst &CBI) {
4004 return visitCallBase(CBI);
4005}

4007/// If this cast does not affect the value passed through the varargs area, we
4008/// can eliminate the use of the cast.
4009static bool isSafeToEliminateVarargsCast(const CallBase &Call,
4010 const DataLayout &DL,
4011 const CastInst *const CI,
4012 const int ix) {
4013 if (!CI->isLosslessCast())
4014 return false;
4015
4016 // If this is a GC intrinsic, avoid munging types. We need types for
4017 // statepoint reconstruction in SelectionDAG.
4018 // TODO: This is probably something which should be expanded to all
4019 // intrinsics since the entire point of intrinsics is that
4020 // they are understandable by the optimizer.
4021 if (isStatepoint(&Call) || isGCRelocate(&Call) || isGCResult(&Call))
4022 return false;
4023
4024 // The size of ByVal or InAlloca arguments is derived from the type, so we
4025 // can't change to a type with a different size. If the size were
4026 // passed explicitly we could avoid this check.
4027 if (!Call.isByValOrInAllocaArgument(ix))
4028 return true;
4029
4030 Type* SrcTy =
4031 cast<PointerType>(CI->getOperand(0)->getType())->getElementType();
4032 Type *DstTy = Call.isByValArgument(ix)
4033 ? Call.getParamByValType(ix)
4034 : cast<PointerType>(CI->getType())->getElementType();
4035 if (!SrcTy->isSized() || !DstTy->isSized())
4036 return false;
4037 if (DL.getTypeAllocSize(SrcTy) != DL.getTypeAllocSize(DstTy))
4038 return false;
4039 return true;
4040}
4041
4042Instruction *InstCombiner::tryOptimizeCall(CallInst *CI) {
4043 if (!CI->getCalledFunction()) return nullptr;
4044
4045 auto InstCombineRAUW = [this](Instruction *From, Value *With) {
4046 replaceInstUsesWith(*From, With);
4047 };
4048 auto InstCombineErase = [this](Instruction *I) {
4049 eraseInstFromFunction(*I);
4050 };
4051 LibCallSimplifier Simplifier(DL, &TLI, ORE, BFI, PSI, InstCombineRAUW,
4052 InstCombineErase);
4053 if (Value *With = Simplifier.optimizeCall(CI)) {
4054 ++NumSimplified;
4055 return CI->use_empty() ? CI : replaceInstUsesWith(*CI, With);
4056 }
4057
4058 return nullptr;
4059}
4060
4061static IntrinsicInst *findInitTrampolineFromAlloca(Value *TrampMem) {
4062 // Strip off at most one level of pointer casts, looking for an alloca. This
4063 // is good enough in practice and simpler than handling any number of casts.
4064 Value *Underlying = TrampMem->stripPointerCasts();
4065 if (Underlying != TrampMem &&
4066 (!Underlying->hasOneUse() || Underlying->user_back() != TrampMem))
4067 return nullptr;
4068 if (!isa<AllocaInst>(Underlying))
4069 return nullptr;
4070
4071 IntrinsicInst *InitTrampoline = nullptr;
4072 for (User *U : TrampMem->users()) {
4073 IntrinsicInst *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(U);
4074 if (!II)
4075 return nullptr;
4076 if (II->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::init_trampoline) {
4077 if (InitTrampoline)
4078 // More than one init_trampoline writes to this value. Give up.
4079 return nullptr;
4080 InitTrampoline = II;
4081 continue;
4082 }
4083 if (II->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::adjust_trampoline)
4084 // Allow any number of calls to adjust.trampoline.
4085 continue;
4086 return nullptr;
4087 }
4088
4089 // No call to init.trampoline found.
4090 if (!InitTrampoline)
4091 return nullptr;
4092
4093 // Check that the alloca is being used in the expected way.
4094 if (InitTrampoline->getOperand(0) != TrampMem)
4095 return nullptr;
4096
4097 return InitTrampoline;
4098}
4099
4100static IntrinsicInst *findInitTrampolineFromBB(IntrinsicInst *AdjustTramp,
4101 Value *TrampMem) {
4102 // Visit all the previous instructions in the basic block, and try to find a
4103 // init.trampoline which has a direct path to the adjust.trampoline.
4104 for (BasicBlock::iterator I = AdjustTramp->getIterator(),
4105 E = AdjustTramp->getParent()->begin();
4106 I != E;) {
4107 Instruction *Inst = &*--I;
4108 if (IntrinsicInst *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(I))
4109 if (II->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::init_trampoline &&
4110 II->getOperand(0) == TrampMem)
4111 return II;
4112 if (Inst->mayWriteToMemory())
4113 return nullptr;
4114 }
4115 return nullptr;
4116}
4117
4118// Given a call to llvm.adjust.trampoline, find and return the corresponding
4119// call to llvm.init.trampoline if the call to the trampoline can be optimized
4120// to a direct call to a function. Otherwise return NULL.
4121static IntrinsicInst *findInitTrampoline(Value *Callee) {
4122 Callee = Callee->stripPointerCasts();
4123 IntrinsicInst *AdjustTramp = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(Callee);
4124 if (!AdjustTramp ||
4125 AdjustTramp->getIntrinsicID() != Intrinsic::adjust_trampoline)
4126 return nullptr;
4127
4128 Value *TrampMem = AdjustTramp->getOperand(0);
4129
4130 if (IntrinsicInst *IT = findInitTrampolineFromAlloca(TrampMem))
4131 return IT;
4132 if (IntrinsicInst *IT = findInitTrampolineFromBB(AdjustTramp, TrampMem))
4133 return IT;
4134 return nullptr;
4135}
4136
4137/// Improvements for call, callbr and invoke instructions.
4138Instruction *InstCombiner::visitCallBase(CallBase &Call) {
4139 if (isAllocLikeFn(&Call, &TLI))
4140 return visitAllocSite(Call);
4141
4142 bool Changed = false;
4143
4144 // Mark any parameters that are known to be non-null with the nonnull
4145 // attribute. This is helpful for inlining calls to functions with null
4146 // checks on their arguments.
4147 SmallVector<unsigned, 4> ArgNos;
4148 unsigned ArgNo = 0;
4149
4150 for (Value *V : Call.args()) {
4151 if (V->getType()->isPointerTy() &&
4152 !Call.paramHasAttr(ArgNo, Attribute::NonNull) &&
4153 isKnownNonZero(V, DL, 0, &AC, &Call, &DT))
4154 ArgNos.push_back(ArgNo);
4155 ArgNo++;
4156 }
4157
4158 assert(ArgNo == Call.arg_size() && "sanity check");
4159
4160 if (!ArgNos.empty()) {
4161 AttributeList AS = Call.getAttributes();
4162 LLVMContext &Ctx = Call.getContext();
4163 AS = AS.addParamAttribute(Ctx, ArgNos,
4164 Attribute::get(Ctx, Attribute::NonNull));
4165 Call.setAttributes(AS);
4166 Changed = true;
4167 }
4168
4169 // If the callee is a pointer to a function, attempt to move any casts to the
4170 // arguments of the call/callbr/invoke.
4171 Value *Callee = Call.getCalledValue();
4172 if (!isa<Function>(Callee) && transformConstExprCastCall(Call))
4173 return nullptr;
4174
4175 if (Function *CalleeF = dyn_cast<Function>(Callee)) {
4176 // Remove the convergent attr on calls when the callee is not convergent.
4177 if (Call.isConvergent() && !CalleeF->isConvergent() &&
4178 !CalleeF->isIntrinsic()) {
4179 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Removing convergent attr from instr " << Call
4180 << "\n");
4181 Call.setNotConvergent();
4182 return &Call;
4183 }
4184
4185 // If the call and callee calling conventions don't match, this call must
4186 // be unreachable, as the call is undefined.
4187 if (CalleeF->getCallingConv() != Call.getCallingConv() &&
4188 // Only do this for calls to a function with a body. A prototype may
4189 // not actually end up matching the implementation's calling conv for a
4190 // variety of reasons (e.g. it may be written in assembly).
4191 !CalleeF->isDeclaration()) {
4192 Instruction *OldCall = &Call;
4193 CreateNonTerminatorUnreachable(OldCall);
4194 // If OldCall does not return void then replaceAllUsesWith undef.
4195 // This allows ValueHandlers and custom metadata to adjust itself.
4196 if (!OldCall->getType()->isVoidTy())
4197 replaceInstUsesWith(*OldCall, UndefValue::get(OldCall->getType()));
4198 if (isa<CallInst>(OldCall))
4199 return eraseInstFromFunction(*OldCall);
4200
4201 // We cannot remove an invoke or a callbr, because it would change thexi
4202 // CFG, just change the callee to a null pointer.
4203 cast<CallBase>(OldCall)->setCalledFunction(
4204 CalleeF->getFunctionType(),
4205 Constant::getNullValue(CalleeF->getType()));
4206 return nullptr;
4207 }
4208 }
4209
4210 if ((isa<ConstantPointerNull>(Callee) &&
4211 !NullPointerIsDefined(Call.getFunction())) ||
4212 isa<UndefValue>(Callee)) {
4213 // If Call does not return void then replaceAllUsesWith undef.
4214 // This allows ValueHandlers and custom metadata to adjust itself.
4215 if (!Call.getType()->isVoidTy())
4216 replaceInstUsesWith(Call, UndefValue::get(Call.getType()));
4217
4218 if (Call.isTerminator()) {
4219 // Can't remove an invoke or callbr because we cannot change the CFG.
4220 return nullptr;
4221 }
4222
4223 // This instruction is not reachable, just remove it.
4224 CreateNonTerminatorUnreachable(&Call);
4225 return eraseInstFromFunction(Call);
4226 }
4227
4228 if (IntrinsicInst *II = findInitTrampoline(Callee))
4229 return transformCallThroughTrampoline(Call, *II);
4230
4231 PointerType *PTy = cast<PointerType>(Callee->getType());
4232 FunctionType *FTy = cast<FunctionType>(PTy->getElementType());
4233 if (FTy->isVarArg()) {
4234 int ix = FTy->getNumParams();
4235 // See if we can optimize any arguments passed through the varargs area of
4236 // the call.
4237 for (auto I = Call.arg_begin() + FTy->getNumParams(), E = Call.arg_end();
4238 I != E; ++I, ++ix) {
4239 CastInst *CI = dyn_cast<CastInst>(*I);
4240 if (CI && isSafeToEliminateVarargsCast(Call, DL, CI, ix)) {
4241 *I = CI->getOperand(0);
4242
4243 // Update the byval type to match the argument type.
4244 if (Call.isByValArgument(ix)) {
4245 Call.removeParamAttr(ix, Attribute::ByVal);
4246 Call.addParamAttr(
4247 ix, Attribute::getWithByValType(
4248 Call.getContext(),
4249 CI->getOperand(0)->getType()->getPointerElementType()));
4250 }
4251 Changed = true;
4252 }
4253 }
4254 }
4255
4256 if (isa<InlineAsm>(Callee) && !Call.doesNotThrow()) {
4257 // Inline asm calls cannot throw - mark them 'nounwind'.
4258 Call.setDoesNotThrow();
4259 Changed = true;
4260 }
4261
4262 // Try to optimize the call if possible, we require DataLayout for most of
4263 // this. None of these calls are seen as possibly dead so go ahead and
4264 // delete the instruction now.
4265 if (CallInst *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(&Call)) {
4266 Instruction *I = tryOptimizeCall(CI);
4267 // If we changed something return the result, etc. Otherwise let
4268 // the fallthrough check.
4269 if (I) return eraseInstFromFunction(*I);
4270 }
4271
4272 return Changed ? &Call : nullptr;
4273}
4274
4275/// If the callee is a constexpr cast of a function, attempt to move the cast to
4276/// the arguments of the call/callbr/invoke.
4277bool InstCombiner::transformConstExprCastCall(CallBase &Call) {
4278 auto *Callee = dyn_cast<Function>(Call.getCalledValue()->stripPointerCasts());
4279 if (!Callee)
4280 return false;
4281
4282 // If this is a call to a thunk function, don't remove the cast. Thunks are
4283 // used to transparently forward all incoming parameters and outgoing return
4284 // values, so it's important to leave the cast in place.
4285 if (Callee->hasFnAttribute("thunk"))
4286 return false;
4287
4288 // If this is a musttail call, the callee's prototype must match the caller's
4289 // prototype with the exception of pointee types. The code below doesn't
4290 // implement that, so we can't do this transform.
4291 // TODO: Do the transform if it only requires adding pointer casts.
4292 if (Call.isMustTailCall())
4293 return false;
4294
4295 Instruction *Caller = &Call;
4296 const AttributeList &CallerPAL = Call.getAttributes();
4297
4298 // Okay, this is a cast from a function to a different type. Unless doing so
4299 // would cause a type conversion of one of our arguments, change this call to
4300 // be a direct call with arguments casted to the appropriate types.
4301 FunctionType *FT = Callee->getFunctionType();
4302 Type *OldRetTy = Caller->getType();
4303 Type *NewRetTy = FT->getReturnType();
4304
4305 // Check to see if we are changing the return type...
4306 if (OldRetTy != NewRetTy) {
4307
4308 if (NewRetTy->isStructTy())
4309 return false; // TODO: Handle multiple return values.
4310
4311 if (!CastInst::isBitOrNoopPointerCastable(NewRetTy, OldRetTy, DL)) {
4312 if (Callee->isDeclaration())
4313 return false; // Cannot transform this return value.
4314
4315 if (!Caller->use_empty() &&
4316 // void -> non-void is handled specially
4317 !NewRetTy->isVoidTy())
4318 return false; // Cannot transform this return value.
4319 }
4320
4321 if (!CallerPAL.isEmpty() && !Caller->use_empty()) {
4322 AttrBuilder RAttrs(CallerPAL, AttributeList::ReturnIndex);
4323 if (RAttrs.overlaps(AttributeFuncs::typeIncompatible(NewRetTy)))
4324 return false; // Attribute not compatible with transformed value.
4325 }
4326
4327 // If the callbase is an invoke/callbr instruction, and the return value is
4328 // used by a PHI node in a successor, we cannot change the return type of
4329 // the call because there is no place to put the cast instruction (without
4330 // breaking the critical edge). Bail out in this case.
4331 if (!Caller->use_empty()) {
4332 if (InvokeInst *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(Caller))
4333 for (User *U : II->users())
4334 if (PHINode *PN = dyn_cast<PHINode>(U))
4335 if (PN->getParent() == II->getNormalDest() ||
4336 PN->getParent() == II->getUnwindDest())
4337 return false;
4338 // FIXME: Be conservative for callbr to avoid a quadratic search.
4339 if (isa<CallBrInst>(Caller))
4340 return false;
4341 }
4342 }
4343
4344 unsigned NumActualArgs = Call.arg_size();
4345 unsigned NumCommonArgs = std::min(FT->getNumParams(), NumActualArgs);
4346
4347 // Prevent us turning:
4348 // declare void @takes_i32_inalloca(i32* inalloca)
4349 // call void bitcast (void (i32*)* @takes_i32_inalloca to void (i32)*)(i32 0)
4350 //
4351 // into:
4352 // call void @takes_i32_inalloca(i32* null)
4353 //
4354 // Similarly, avoid folding away bitcasts of byval calls.
4355 if (Callee->getAttributes().hasAttrSomewhere(Attribute::InAlloca) ||
4356 Callee->getAttributes().hasAttrSomewhere(Attribute::ByVal))
4357 return false;
4358
4359 auto AI = Call.arg_begin();
4360 for (unsigned i = 0, e = NumCommonArgs; i != e; ++i, ++AI) {
4361 Type *ParamTy = FT->getParamType(i);
4362 Type *ActTy = (*AI)->getType();
4363
4364 if (!CastInst::isBitOrNoopPointerCastable(ActTy, ParamTy, DL))
4365 return false; // Cannot transform this parameter value.
4366
4367 if (AttrBuilder(CallerPAL.getParamAttributes(i))
4368 .overlaps(AttributeFuncs::typeIncompatible(ParamTy)))
4369 return false; // Attribute not compatible with transformed value.
4370
4371 if (Call.isInAllocaArgument(i))
4372 return false; // Cannot transform to and from inalloca.
4373
4374 // If the parameter is passed as a byval argument, then we have to have a
4375 // sized type and the sized type has to have the same size as the old type.
4376 if (ParamTy != ActTy && CallerPAL.hasParamAttribute(i, Attribute::ByVal)) {
4377 PointerType *ParamPTy = dyn_cast<PointerType>(ParamTy);
4378 if (!ParamPTy || !ParamPTy->getElementType()->isSized())
4379 return false;
4380
4381 Type *CurElTy = Call.getParamByValType(i);
4382 if (DL.getTypeAllocSize(CurElTy) !=
4383 DL.getTypeAllocSize(ParamPTy->getElementType()))
4384 return false;
4385 }
4386 }
4387
4388 if (Callee->isDeclaration()) {
4389 // Do not delete arguments unless we have a function body.
4390 if (FT->getNumParams() < NumActualArgs && !FT->isVarArg())
4391 return false;
4392
4393 // If the callee is just a declaration, don't change the varargsness of the
4394 // call. We don't want to introduce a varargs call where one doesn't
4395 // already exist.
4396 PointerType *APTy = cast<PointerType>(Call.getCalledValue()->getType());
4397 if (FT->isVarArg()!=cast<FunctionType>(APTy->getElementType())->isVarArg())
4398 return false;
4399
4400 // If both the callee and the cast type are varargs, we still have to make
4401 // sure the number of fixed parameters are the same or we have the same
4402 // ABI issues as if we introduce a varargs call.
4403 if (FT->isVarArg() &&
4404 cast<FunctionType>(APTy->getElementType())->isVarArg() &&
4405 FT->getNumParams() !=
4406 cast<FunctionType>(APTy->getElementType())->getNumParams())
4407 return false;
4408 }
4409
4410 if (FT->getNumParams() < NumActualArgs && FT->isVarArg() &&
4411 !CallerPAL.isEmpty()) {
4412 // In this case we have more arguments than the new function type, but we
4413 // won't be dropping them. Check that these extra arguments have attributes
4414 // that are compatible with being a vararg call argument.
4415 unsigned SRetIdx;
4416 if (CallerPAL.hasAttrSomewhere(Attribute::StructRet, &SRetIdx) &&
4417 SRetIdx > FT->getNumParams())
4418 return false;
4419 }
4420
4421 // Okay, we decided that this is a safe thing to do: go ahead and start
4422 // inserting cast instructions as necessary.
4423 SmallVector<Value *, 8> Args;
4424 SmallVector<AttributeSet, 8> ArgAttrs;
4425 Args.reserve(NumActualArgs);
4426 ArgAttrs.reserve(NumActualArgs);
4427
4428 // Get any return attributes.
4429 AttrBuilder RAttrs(CallerPAL, AttributeList::ReturnIndex);
4430
4431 // If the return value is not being used, the type may not be compatible
4432 // with the existing attributes. Wipe out any problematic attributes.
4433 RAttrs.remove(AttributeFuncs::typeIncompatible(NewRetTy));
4434
4435 LLVMContext &Ctx = Call.getContext();
4436 AI = Call.arg_begin();
4437 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumCommonArgs; ++i, ++AI) {
4438 Type *ParamTy = FT->getParamType(i);
4439
4440 Value *NewArg = *AI;
4441 if ((*AI)->getType() != ParamTy)
4442 NewArg = Builder.CreateBitOrPointerCast(*AI, ParamTy);
4443 Args.push_back(NewArg);
4444
4445 // Add any parameter attributes.
4446 if (CallerPAL.hasParamAttribute(i, Attribute::ByVal)) {
4447 AttrBuilder AB(CallerPAL.getParamAttributes(i));
4448 AB.addByValAttr(NewArg->getType()->getPointerElementType());
4449 ArgAttrs.push_back(AttributeSet::get(Ctx, AB));
4450 } else
4451 ArgAttrs.push_back(CallerPAL.getParamAttributes(i));
4452 }
4453
4454 // If the function takes more arguments than the call was taking, add them
4455 // now.
4456 for (unsigned i = NumCommonArgs; i != FT->getNumParams(); ++i) {
4457 Args.push_back(Constant::getNullValue(FT->getParamType(i)));
4458 ArgAttrs.push_back(AttributeSet());
4459 }
4460
4461 // If we are removing arguments to the function, emit an obnoxious warning.
4462 if (FT->getNumParams() < NumActualArgs) {
4463 // TODO: if (!FT->isVarArg()) this call may be unreachable. PR14722
4464 if (FT->isVarArg()) {
4465 // Add all of the arguments in their promoted form to the arg list.
4466 for (unsigned i = FT->getNumParams(); i != NumActualArgs; ++i, ++AI) {
4467 Type *PTy = getPromotedType((*AI)->getType());
4468 Value *NewArg = *AI;
4469 if (PTy != (*AI)->getType()) {
4470 // Must promote to pass through va_arg area!
4471 Instruction::CastOps opcode =
4472 CastInst::getCastOpcode(*AI, false, PTy, false);
4473 NewArg = Builder.CreateCast(opcode, *AI, PTy);
4474 }
4475 Args.push_back(NewArg);
4476
4477 // Add any parameter attributes.
4478 ArgAttrs.push_back(CallerPAL.getParamAttributes(i));
4479 }
4480 }
4481 }
4482
4483 AttributeSet FnAttrs = CallerPAL.getFnAttributes();
4484
4485 if (NewRetTy->isVoidTy())
4486 Caller->setName(""); // Void type should not have a name.
4487
4488 assert((ArgAttrs.size() == FT->getNumParams() || FT->isVarArg()) &&
4489 "missing argument attributes");
4490 AttributeList NewCallerPAL = AttributeList::get(
4491 Ctx, FnAttrs, AttributeSet::get(Ctx, RAttrs), ArgAttrs);
4492
4493 SmallVector<OperandBundleDef, 1> OpBundles;
4494 Call.getOperandBundlesAsDefs(OpBundles);
4495
4496 CallBase *NewCall;
4497 if (InvokeInst *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(Caller)) {
4498 NewCall = Builder.CreateInvoke(Callee, II->getNormalDest(),
4499 II->getUnwindDest(), Args, OpBundles);
4500 } else if (CallBrInst *CBI = dyn_cast<CallBrInst>(Caller)) {
4501 NewCall = Builder.CreateCallBr(Callee, CBI->getDefaultDest(),
4502 CBI->getIndirectDests(), Args, OpBundles);
4503 } else {
4504 NewCall = Builder.CreateCall(Callee, Args, OpBundles);
4505 cast<CallInst>(NewCall)->setTailCallKind(
4506 cast<CallInst>(Caller)->getTailCallKind());
4507 }
4508 NewCall->takeName(Caller);
4509 NewCall->setCallingConv(Call.getCallingConv());
4510 NewCall->setAttributes(NewCallerPAL);
4511
4512 // Preserve the weight metadata for the new call instruction. The metadata
4513 // is used by SamplePGO to check callsite's hotness.
4514 uint64_t W;
4515 if (Caller->extractProfTotalWeight(W))
4516 NewCall->setProfWeight(W);
4517
4518 // Insert a cast of the return type as necessary.
4519 Instruction *NC = NewCall;
4520 Value *NV = NC;
4521 if (OldRetTy != NV->getType() && !Caller->use_empty()) {
4522 if (!NV->getType()->isVoidTy()) {
4523 NV = NC = CastInst::CreateBitOrPointerCast(NC, OldRetTy);
4524 NC->setDebugLoc(Caller->getDebugLoc());
4525
4526 // If this is an invoke/callbr instruction, we should insert it after the
4527 // first non-phi instruction in the normal successor block.
4528 if (InvokeInst *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(Caller)) {
4529 BasicBlock::iterator I = II->getNormalDest()->getFirstInsertionPt();
4530 InsertNewInstBefore(NC, *I);
4531 } else if (CallBrInst *CBI = dyn_cast<CallBrInst>(Caller)) {
4532 BasicBlock::iterator I = CBI->getDefaultDest()->getFirstInsertionPt();
4533 InsertNewInstBefore(NC, *I);
4534 } else {
4535 // Otherwise, it's a call, just insert cast right after the call.
4536 InsertNewInstBefore(NC, *Caller);
4537 }
4538 Worklist.AddUsersToWorkList(*Caller);
4539 } else {
4540 NV = UndefValue::get(Caller->getType());
4541 }
4542 }
4543
4544 if (!Caller->use_empty())
4545 replaceInstUsesWith(*Caller, NV);
4546 else if (Caller->hasValueHandle()) {
4547 if (OldRetTy == NV->getType())
4548 ValueHandleBase::ValueIsRAUWd(Caller, NV);
4549 else
4550 // We cannot call ValueIsRAUWd with a different type, and the
4551 // actual tracked value will disappear.
4552 ValueHandleBase::ValueIsDeleted(Caller);
4553 }
4554
4555 eraseInstFromFunction(*Caller);
4556 return true;
4557}
4558
4559/// Turn a call to a function created by init_trampoline / adjust_trampoline
4560/// intrinsic pair into a direct call to the underlying function.
4561Instruction *
4562InstCombiner::transformCallThroughTrampoline(CallBase &Call,
4563 IntrinsicInst &Tramp) {
4564 Value *Callee = Call.getCalledValue();
4565 Type *CalleeTy = Callee->getType();
4566 FunctionType *FTy = Call.getFunctionType();
4567 AttributeList Attrs = Call.getAttributes();
4568
4569 // If the call already has the 'nest' attribute somewhere then give up -
4570 // otherwise 'nest' would occur twice after splicing in the chain.
4571 if (Attrs.hasAttrSomewhere(Attribute::Nest))
4572 return nullptr;
4573
4574 Function *NestF = cast<Function>(Tramp.getArgOperand(1)->stripPointerCasts());
4575 FunctionType *NestFTy = NestF->getFunctionType();
4576
4577 AttributeList NestAttrs = NestF->getAttributes();
4578 if (!NestAttrs.isEmpty()) {
4579 unsigned NestArgNo = 0;
4580 Type *NestTy = nullptr;
4581 AttributeSet NestAttr;
4582
4583 // Look for a parameter marked with the 'nest' attribute.
4584 for (FunctionType::param_iterator I = NestFTy->param_begin(),
4585 E = NestFTy->param_end();
4586 I != E; ++NestArgNo, ++I) {
4587 AttributeSet AS = NestAttrs.getParamAttributes(NestArgNo);
4588 if (AS.hasAttribute(Attribute::Nest)) {
4589 // Record the parameter type and any other attributes.
4590 NestTy = *I;
4591 NestAttr = AS;
4592 break;
4593 }
4594 }
4595
4596 if (NestTy) {
4597 std::vector<Value*> NewArgs;
4598 std::vector<AttributeSet> NewArgAttrs;
4599 NewArgs.reserve(Call.arg_size() + 1);
4600 NewArgAttrs.reserve(Call.arg_size());
4601
4602 // Insert the nest argument into the call argument list, which may
4603 // mean appending it. Likewise for attributes.
4604
4605 {
4606 unsigned ArgNo = 0;
4607 auto I = Call.arg_begin(), E = Call.arg_end();
4608 do {
4609 if (ArgNo == NestArgNo) {
4610 // Add the chain argument and attributes.
4611 Value *NestVal = Tramp.getArgOperand(2);
4612 if (NestVal->getType() != NestTy)
4613 NestVal = Builder.CreateBitCast(NestVal, NestTy, "nest");
4614 NewArgs.push_back(NestVal);
4615 NewArgAttrs.push_back(NestAttr);
4616 }
4617
4618 if (I == E)
4619 break;
4620
4621 // Add the original argument and attributes.
4622 NewArgs.push_back(*I);
4623 NewArgAttrs.push_back(Attrs.getParamAttributes(ArgNo));
4624
4625 ++ArgNo;
4626 ++I;
4627 } while (true);
4628 }
4629
4630 // The trampoline may have been bitcast to a bogus type (FTy).
4631 // Handle this by synthesizing a new function type, equal to FTy
4632 // with the chain parameter inserted.
4633
4634 std::vector<Type*> NewTypes;
4635 NewTypes.reserve(FTy->getNumParams()+1);
4636
4637 // Insert the chain's type into the list of parameter types, which may
4638 // mean appending it.
4639 {
4640 unsigned ArgNo = 0;
4641 FunctionType::param_iterator I = FTy->param_begin(),
4642 E = FTy->param_end();
4643
4644 do {
4645 if (ArgNo == NestArgNo)
4646 // Add the chain's type.
4647 NewTypes.push_back(NestTy);
4648
4649 if (I == E)
4650 break;
4651
4652 // Add the original type.
4653 NewTypes.push_back(*I);
4654
4655 ++ArgNo;
4656 ++I;
4657 } while (true);
4658 }
4659
4660 // Replace the trampoline call with a direct call. Let the generic
4661 // code sort out any function type mismatches.
4662 FunctionType *NewFTy = FunctionType::get(FTy->getReturnType(), NewTypes,
4663 FTy->isVarArg());
4664 Constant *NewCallee =
4665 NestF->getType() == PointerType::getUnqual(NewFTy) ?
4666 NestF : ConstantExpr::getBitCast(NestF,
4667 PointerType::getUnqual(NewFTy));
4668 AttributeList NewPAL =
4669 AttributeList::get(FTy->getContext(), Attrs.getFnAttributes(),
4670 Attrs.getRetAttributes(), NewArgAttrs);
4671
4672 SmallVector<OperandBundleDef, 1> OpBundles;
4673 Call.getOperandBundlesAsDefs(OpBundles);
4674
4675 Instruction *NewCaller;
4676 if (InvokeInst *II = dyn_cast<InvokeInst>(&Call)) {
4677 NewCaller = InvokeInst::Create(NewFTy, NewCallee,
4678 II->getNormalDest(), II->getUnwindDest(),
4679 NewArgs, OpBundles);
4680 cast<InvokeInst>(NewCaller)->setCallingConv(II->getCallingConv());
4681 cast<InvokeInst>(NewCaller)->setAttributes(NewPAL);
4682 } else if (CallBrInst *CBI = dyn_cast<CallBrInst>(&Call)) {
4683 NewCaller =
4684 CallBrInst::Create(NewFTy, NewCallee, CBI->getDefaultDest(),
4685 CBI->getIndirectDests(), NewArgs, OpBundles);
4686 cast<CallBrInst>(NewCaller)->setCallingConv(CBI->getCallingConv());
4687 cast<CallBrInst>(NewCaller)->setAttributes(NewPAL);
4688 } else {
4689 NewCaller = CallInst::Create(NewFTy, NewCallee, NewArgs, OpBundles);
4690 cast<CallInst>(NewCaller)->setTailCallKind(
4691 cast<CallInst>(Call).getTailCallKind());
4692 cast<CallInst>(NewCaller)->setCallingConv(
4693 cast<CallInst>(Call).getCallingConv());
4694 cast<CallInst>(NewCaller)->setAttributes(NewPAL);
4695 }
4696 NewCaller->setDebugLoc(Call.getDebugLoc());
4697
4698 return NewCaller;
4699 }
4700 }
4701
4702 // Replace the trampoline call with a direct call. Since there is no 'nest'
4703 // parameter, there is no need to adjust the argument list. Let the generic
4704 // code sort out any function type mismatches.
4705 Constant *NewCallee = ConstantExpr::getBitCast(NestF, CalleeTy);
4706 Call.setCalledFunction(FTy, NewCallee);
4707 return &Call;
4708}
